<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-29T12:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-29T12:29:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/140</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d273fn2">Printed in full, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_6">p. 6</ref>.</note></seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-29T20:00:00+02:31"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                            1917, 8 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 30, 6.30
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1236. … Callers [two Russian Ministers] told me Ministry resented
                                suggestion of British Ambassador that Siberian Railway be turned
                                over to us, saying Russia does not need nurses but had agreed
                                directly with us concerning Vladivostok and had <pb facs="0239" n="189" xml:id="pg_189"/> candidly told me yesterday of their
                                wishes and requirements in White Sea. You see their sensitiveness
                                especially [as concerns] England.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>